For clunky earrings or earrings with considerable girth, store in a large box instead of trying to cram them in the book. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/69/Repurpose-a-Datebook-Into-an-Earring-Storage-Book-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Repurpose-a-Datebook-Into-an-Earring-Storage-Book-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/69/Repurpose-a-Datebook-Into-an-Earring-Storage-Book-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Repurpose-a-Datebook-Into-an-Earring-Storage-Book-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":316,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":521.978021978022,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
