Once you're certain of the size required, choose a book that meets this need. The book must be in good condition and needs to be one that you can re-use. Look for a sturdy cover and binding. An old organizer that is worn or misshapen won’t work very well for this project. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1f/Repurpose-a-Datebook-Into-an-Earring-Storage-Book-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Repurpose-a-Datebook-Into-an-Earring-Storage-Book-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1f/Repurpose-a-Datebook-Into-an-Earring-Storage-Book-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Repurpose-a-Datebook-Into-an-Earring-Storage-Book-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
